# ============================================================================
# Pulse API — Request Collection
# ============================================================================
#
# This file is your dev-time control panel for the API. Every endpoint is
# documented here with a working example body.
#
# How to use it:
#   VS Code:    install the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) — then
#               click "Send Request" above any `###` block below.
#   JetBrains:  open and click the "▶" gutter icon on any request.
#   Thunder Client / Bruno: import this file as a collection.
#
# Variables (edit these at the top to match your local data):
#   @baseUrl    — your running API. Default assumes `docker compose up`.
#   @projectId  — used in all path-scoped requests. Set to whatever id your
#                 most-recently-created project has.
#   @modelName  — model name to log usage against. Must exist in /models.
#
# QUICKSTART section starts at line 36 — most-used requests in workflow order.
# DETAILED CRUD sections start at line 105 — full coverage including error cases.
# See api.md for a navigation table with line numbers.
# ============================================================================

@baseUrl    = http://localhost:8080
@projectId  = 1
@modelName  = gpt-4o
@modelId    = 1


### Health Check — confirm the server is reachable
GET {{baseUrl}}/healthz


# ============================================================================
# QUICKSTART — top 9 most-used endpoints, in workflow order
# ============================================================================
# Click Send on these top-to-bottom on a fresh DB and you'll have a project,
# a usage event recorded against it, the events listed back, and the budget
# updated. After this, scroll past line 175 for full CRUD + error cases.
# ============================================================================

### [1] Create Project — captured as `createProject` so chained requests
###     below can reference {{createProject.response.body.$.id}}.
# @name createProject
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Project",
  "daily_budget_dollars": 5.00,
  "monthly_budget_dollars": 100.00,
  "total_budget_dollars": 1000.00
}

### [2] List Projects — see what exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects

### [3] Get Project By ID — using the captured id from [1]
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{createProject.response.body.$.id}}

### [4] Add Model — only needed if your call uses a model not in the seeded list
# @name createModel
POST {{baseUrl}}/models
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "custom-model-x",
  "input_per_million_cents": 50,
  "output_per_million_cents": 200
}

### [5] List Models — see all models (seeded + custom)
GET {{baseUrl}}/models

### [6] Add Usage Event — log a call. cost_dollars is computed server-side.
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "{{modelName}}",
  "tokens_in": 1500,
  "tokens_out": 500,
  "latency_ms": 350,
  "tag": "chat"
}

### [7] List Usage Events — cursor-paginated, newest first
# @name firstPage
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/events

### [8] Update Project Budget — PATCH partial update
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "daily_budget_dollars": 10.00
}

### [9] GET Project — see live budget_status (spend vs limits, % used, flags)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}


# ============================================================================
# DETAILED CRUD — full coverage including variations + error cases
# ============================================================================


### ----------------------------------------------------
### PROJECTS — variations and errors
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Create Project with only daily budget — monthly/total left null
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Daily Only Project",
  "daily_budget_dollars": 2.00
}

### Create Project with no budgets at all — all enforcement disabled
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Unlimited Project"
}

### Update Project — set all three budgets at once
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "daily_budget_dollars": 10.00,
  "monthly_budget_dollars": 200.00,
  "total_budget_dollars": 2000.00
}

### Update Project — rename + bump monthly budget
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Project (renamed)",
  "monthly_budget_dollars": 150.00
}

### Delete Project (soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}

### --- error cases ---

### Error - Create Project with duplicate name
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Project",
  "daily_budget_dollars": 1.00
}

### Error - Create Project with empty name
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "daily_budget_dollars": 1.00
}

### Error - Create Project with negative budget
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Budget Project",
  "daily_budget_dollars": -1.00
}

### Error - Get Non-Existent Project
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/9999

### Error - Get Soft-Deleted Project (after running DELETE above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}


### ----------------------------------------------------
### MODELS — variations and errors
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Get Model By ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/models/{{modelId}}

### Update Model (Partial — output pricing only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/models/{{createModel.response.body.$.id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "output_per_million_cents": 250
}

### Delete Model
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/models/{{createModel.response.body.$.id}}

### --- error cases ---

### Error - Create Model with duplicate name (run AFTER quickstart [4])
POST {{baseUrl}}/models
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "custom-model-x",
  "input_per_million_cents": 50,
  "output_per_million_cents": 200
}

### Error - Create Model with negative pricing
POST {{baseUrl}}/models
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "bad-price-model",
  "input_per_million_cents": -10,
  "output_per_million_cents": 200
}

### Error - Get Non-Existent Model
GET {{baseUrl}}/models/9999


### ----------------------------------------------------
### USAGE — variations and errors
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Add Usage — asymmetric tokens (lots of input, little output)
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "tokens_in": 5000,
  "tokens_out": 200,
  "latency_ms": 300,
  "tag": "summarize"
}

### Add Usage — latency_ms omitted (it's optional/nullable)
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "tokens_in": 100,
  "tokens_out": 50,
  "tag": "untimed"
}

### Add Usage — different tag, smaller call
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gemini-2.5-flash",
  "tokens_in": 500,
  "tokens_out": 200,
  "latency_ms": 400,
  "tag": "embedding"
}

### Push spend OVER the daily $5 budget — single massive call (~$90.00).
### This crosses the budget instantly. Then GET /projects/{id} to see
### budget_status.daily.over_budget = true.
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "claude-opus-4-20250514",
  "tokens_in": 1000000,
  "tokens_out": 1000000,
  "latency_ms": 3000,
  "tag": "bulk"
}

### --- error cases ---

### Error - Add Usage with unknown model
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "not-a-real-model",
  "tokens_in": 100,
  "tokens_out": 50,
  "latency_ms": 200,
  "tag": "test"
}

### Error - Add Usage to non-existent project
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/9999/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "{{modelName}}",
  "tokens_in": 100,
  "tokens_out": 50,
  "latency_ms": 200,
  "tag": "test"
}

### Error - Add Usage with non-numeric project ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/abc/usage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "{{modelName}}",
  "tokens_in": 100,
  "tokens_out": 50,
  "latency_ms": 200,
  "tag": "test"
}


### ----------------------------------------------------
### USAGE STATS (Redis cache → SQL fallback)
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Get Daily Stats — today (reads from Redis cache if warm)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/daily

### Get Daily Stats — specific date
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/daily?date=2026-04-28

### Get Monthly Stats — current month (cache-then-SQL for cost; SQL only for tokens)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/monthly

### Get Monthly Stats — specific month
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/monthly?month=2026-04

### Get Stats for project with no usage (returns zeros, not an error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/2/usage/daily

### Get Stats for non-existent project (also returns zeros)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/9999/usage/daily

### Recent Avg Latency — average of last N events, ignoring null latency_ms.
### Used by the Grafana Avg Latency panel. Limit defaults to 5.
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/recent-latency?limit=5

### --- error cases ---

### Error - Daily Stats with invalid date format
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/daily?date=28-04-2026

### Error - Monthly Stats with invalid month format
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/monthly?month=2026/04


### ----------------------------------------------------
### USAGE RANGE & SUMMARY (SQL-only, no cache)
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Project Range — single project, arbitrary date window
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-30

### Project Range — same from/to (one-day window, equivalent to /daily)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-28&to=2026-04-28

### Project Range — RFC3339 timestamps (precise window, e.g. a 4-hour slice)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-28T10:00:00Z&to=2026-04-28T14:00:00Z

### Project Range — mixed date + timestamp (from = start of day, to = exact)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-28&to=2026-04-28T12:00:00Z

### Project Range — window with no usage (returns zeros)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2020-01-01&to=2020-01-31

### Usage Summary — all projects with per-project breakdown + totals
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/summary?from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-30

### Usage Summary — single day across all projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/summary?from=2026-04-28&to=2026-04-28

### Usage Summary — empty window (empty projects array, zero totals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/summary?from=2020-01-01&to=2020-01-31

### --- error cases ---

### Error - Project Range missing from
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?to=2026-04-30

### Error - Project Range missing to
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-01

### Error - Project Range from > to
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=2026-04-30&to=2026-04-01

### Error - Project Range invalid date format
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/range?from=04-01-2026&to=04-30-2026

### Error - Usage Summary missing both params
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/summary

### Error - Usage Summary with invalid date
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/summary?from=not-a-date&to=2026-04-30


### ----------------------------------------------------
### USAGE EVENTS — pagination variations and errors
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Project events — explicit date range + smaller page
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/events?from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-30&limit=10

### Project events — next page (chained from QUICKSTART [7] firstPage)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/usage/events?cursor={{firstPage.response.body.$.next_cursor}}

### All projects — first page, all-time
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events

### All projects — scoped to today with small page
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events?from=2026-04-28&to=2026-04-28&limit=5

### Limit boundary — request 500, server caps at 100
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events?limit=500

### --- error cases ---

### Error - invalid cursor
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events?cursor=not-a-real-cursor

### Error - invalid limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events?limit=abc

### Error - from > to
GET {{baseUrl}}/usage/events?from=2026-04-28&to=2026-04-01
